President Obama has nominated David Jeremiah Barron to serve on the United States Court of Appeals for the First Circuit. Barron is currently a professor at Harvard Law School and has previously served as the Acting Assistant Attorney General of the Office of Legal Counsel at the Department of Justice. He has a strong legal background, having clerked for Judge Stephen R. Reinhardt of the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit and Justice John Paul Stevens of the Supreme Court of the United States. Barron has also received awards for his service, including the National Intelligence Exceptional Achievement Medal and the Office of the Secretary of Defense Medal for Exceptional Public Service. He is highly regarded and is expected to be a diligent and esteemed addition to the First Circuit bench.